channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: Lawmakers Visit Trump Assassination Attempt Site, Blow Apart Kim Cheatle's 'Sloped Roof' Excuse
Kamala Harris visiting Milwaukee for first campaign rally since launching presidential bid
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris will hold a rally on Tuesday in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, after launching her presidential campaign following President Biden's departure from the race.

item.title: Kamala Harris Campaign Raises More Than $100 Million
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris' campaign raised more than $100 million between Sunday afternoon and Monday evening, The Hill reported Tuesday, without naming its sources.

item.title: GOP Rep. Nancy Mace Files Motion to Impeach Secret Service Director Kim Cheatle
Top five moments from Secret Service director's hours-long grilling after Trump assassination attempt
item.description: U.S. Secret Service Director Kimberly Cheatle testified for hours on Capitol Hill Monday, facing a grilling from lawmakers on both sides of the aisle.

item.title: Biden's Economic Impact May Be Felt Long After His Presidency
item.description: U.S. President Joe Biden may not have gotten much credit politically for the thousands of grants and public investments his administration showered across the country, with airport or road projects in places like South Carolina and Wyoming unlikely to dent former President...

item.title: Rep. Mike Waltz Gives Secret Service Director Kimberly Cheatle No Quarter in Oversight Hearing
Kamala Harris doesn't answer whether Biden is fit for office
item.description: Vice President Harris remained silent when asked if President Biden is currently capable of serving as president.

item.title: Biden Expected to Meet Netanyahu on Thursday at WH
item.description: President Joe Biden is expected to meet Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Thursday at the White House, a U.S. official said on Monday.Biden has been battling COVID-19 since last Wednesday but is returning to Washington on Tuesday from his beach house in Delaware....

item.title: GOP Senator Becomes First Member of Congress to Demand Kamala, Cabinet Invoke 25th Amendment
The race to define Kamala Harris, as Pelosi endorses her and no challengers emerge
item.description: While Vice President Kamala Harris has name recognition and experience in the White House, she faces an uphill battle against Donald Trump - can she succeed?

item.title: Harris Surpasses Number of Delegates Needed for Nomination: Campaign Sources
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris surpassed the number of delegates needed to claim the Democratic presidential nomination on Monday night, campaign sources told Reuters.According to an Associated Press tally, Harris had 2,214 delegates, well beyond the simple majority needed to...

item.title: Eric Holder Tapped to Head up VP Selection Committee for Kamala Harris for President
Biden makes bizarre call in to Harris headquarters hours after dropping out of race
item.description: President Biden called in to the campaign of Vice President Harris on Monday to give his support and praise her candidacy.

item.title: Rep. Steube Moves to Impeach Secret Service Chief
item.description: Rep. Greg Steube, R-Fla., filed articles of impeachment Monday against Secret Service Director Kimberly Cheatle for "enabling" the assassination attempt on Republican nominee Donald Trump.
